(1) Form Control
-----------------
==> Give textual form controls like <input>s and <textarea>s an upgrade with custom styles, sizing, focus states, and more.


(2) Form Control Sample
------------------------

    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">
        Name
      </label>
      <input type="text" class="form-control" id="formControl" />
    </div>
    
    
(2) Form Control Sizing [form-control-sm , form-control-lg]
------------------------

    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">Name</label>
      <input type="text" class="form-control" id="formControl" />
    </div>
    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">Name</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control form-control-sm"
        id="formControl"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">Name</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control form-control-lg"
        id="formControl"
      />
    </div>
    
    
(3) Readonly Form Control
--------------------------

    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">Name</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control"
        value="Magdy Mohammed"
        id="formControl"
        readonly
      />
    </div>
    
    
(4) Form Control Readonly plain text
-------------------------------------

    <div class="p-4">
      <label for="formControl" class="form-label">Name</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control-plaintext"
        value="Magdy Mohammed"
        id="formControl"
      />
    </div>
    
    
(5) Form Control Color
------------------------

      <input
        type="color"
        class="form-control form-control-color"
        id="formControl"
      />
      
(6) Datalists
-----------------
==> Datalists allow you to create a group of <option>s that can be accessed (and autocompleted) from within an <input>. These are similar to <select> elements.


    <div class="p-4">
      <input
        class="form-control"
        list="datalistOptions"
        placeholder="Type to search..."
      />
      <datalist id="datalistOptions">
        <option value="San Francisco"> </option>
        <option value="New York"> </option>
        <option value="Seattle"> </option>
        <option value="Los Angeles"> </option>
        <option value="Chicago"> </option>
      </datalist>
    </div>
